        <h3 class="publication-title">Customer-Level Aggregation: The Imperative for Reliable Non-Technical Loss Detection Amidst Row-Level Analysis Pitfalls</h3>
        <p class="publication-authors">M. Küçük, H. Coşkun, <strong>M. Biricik</strong>, B. E. Bülbül</p>
        <p class="publication-venue">Proceedings of the 60th International Universities Power Engineering Conference (UPEC), IEEE, 2025</p>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <h4>Abstract</h4>
          <p>This paper addresses critical challenges in non-technical loss detection within power distribution systems by proposing customer-level aggregation methods. The research demonstrates significant improvements in detection accuracy while avoiding common pitfalls associated with row-level analysis approaches in electricity theft identification.</p>
          
          <h4>Key Contributions</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Novel customer-level aggregation methodology for electricity theft detection</li>
            <li>Comprehensive analysis of row-level analysis limitations and biases</li>
            <li>Development of robust machine learning pipeline for anomaly detection</li>
            <li>Empirical validation using real-world power distribution data</li>
          </ul>
          
